# Load Issue - Get Issue Context

Fetch and load issue context from Linear or GitHub into your Claude conversation.

## Usage

```bash
# Load from current branch (auto-detects issue ID)
/load-issue

# Load specific Linear issue
/load-issue METR-123

# Load specific GitHub issue
/load-issue gh#456

# Load with full details
/load-issue METR-123 --full

# Load and include linked issues
/load-issue METR-123 --linked
```

## What It Does

1. **Detect issue ID:**
   - From current branch name (e.g., METR-123/fix-auth)
   - Or use provided issue ID (METR-123 or gh#456)

2. **Fetch issue details via MCP:**
   - Title and description
   - Current status and priority
   - Assignees and due date
   - Linked pull requests
   - Comments and activity
   - Acceptance criteria

3. **Format and display:**
   - Render issue as markdown in conversation
   - Include issue metadata
   - Show related issues or PRs
   - Highlight acceptance criteria

4. **Context awareness:**
   - Link to issue tracker
   - Show estimated time to completion
   - Display team assignments

